"Based on the retrieved social media posts, the following facts and claims regarding Ferguson are summarized using the three-state evidence model:\n\n**Verified-Fact**\n*   **Media Sensitivity and Terminology:** There is significant sensitivity among people in Ferguson regarding media descriptions of \"rioting.\" A verified user notes that behavior accurately described as rioting occurred only on Sunday, implying that subsequent events may have been mischaracterized by media outlets [4].\n\n**Informal-but-Genuine**\n*   **Solidarity:** Verified users have expressed public solidarity with the community in Ferguson [3].\n*   **Police Report Availability:** An unverified user shared a link claiming to be a full police report on Mike Brown and Ferguson, though the text itself was redacted in the post metadata [2].\n\n**Unverified-Rumour**\n*   **Signal Jamming Allegations:** Claims that police are using jammers to take down livestreams in Ferguson are present but remain unverified. This claim originates from a single source with no corroborating cluster support, despite moderate trust metrics [1].\n*   **Related Incidents in LA:** A claim that another black man was killed by police in Los Angeles during the Ferguson protests, receiving little news coverage, is presented as an observational opinion rather than a confirmed fact within this dataset [5]."